Work done during expansion at constant pressure can be calculated using the formula:<div></div>$$
W=-P \Delta V
$$<div></div>


Using the ideal gas law, $P V=n R T$<div></div>
so, $P \Delta V=\Delta n R T$<div></div>

$$
\therefore W=-\Delta n R T
$$

